INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_tip4950','letter','1763-02-14','Harvard College','MA','US','Timothy','Pickering','','Timothy','Pickering','Sr','individual','','It is the common opinion of people that to play a game at cards is (almost) an unpardonable crime. But what renders it more odious than other diversions ?','ltr_tip4950.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life Timothy Pickering. by His Son, Octavius Pickering. Volume I. 1867');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_tip4951','letter','1772-07-08','Salem','MA','US','Timothy','Pickering','','Andrew','Oliver','','individual','','You must, Sir, ere now apprehend the design of this letter, if you have never heard that I am desirous of being appointed joint Clerk with Mr. Bowditch.','ltr_tip4951.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life Timothy Pickering. by His Son, Octavius Pickering. Volume I. 1867');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_tip4952','letter','1774-03-21','Salem','MA','US','Timothy','Pickering','','James','Latham','','individual','','When you have informed me of your design in making this request, I shall be able to give you a further answer. ','ltr_tip4952.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life Timothy Pickering. by His Son, Octavius Pickering. Volume I. 1867');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_tip4953','letter','1774-08-25','Salem','MA','US','Timothy','Pickering','','Paine','Wingate','','individual','','It will he agreeable to you to have an authentic account of the recent transactions in this town.','ltr_tip4953.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life Timothy Pickering. by His Son, Octavius Pickering. Volume I. 1867');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_tip4954','letter','1812-04-06','Wenham','MA','US','Timothy','Pickering','','Jacob','Dodge','','individual','','...induces me to present to you my correspondence with Governor Sullivan, in which I have stated the circumstances respecting my conduct on the day of the battle of Lexington, not a syllable of which, to my knowledge, has ever been contradicted','ltr_tip4954.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life Timothy Pickering. by His Son, Octavius Pickering. Volume I. 1867');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_tip4955','letter','1775-04-26','Salem','MA','US','Timothy','Pickering','','Paine','Wingate','','individual','','I am still of opinion that a pacification upon honorable terms is practicable. This opinion I declared in the council of war at Cambridge last Thursday','ltr_tip4955.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life Timothy Pickering. by His Son, Octavius Pickering. Volume I. 1867');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_tip4956','letter','1775-05-02','Salem','MA','US','Timothy','Pickering','','','Higginson','','individual','','You as rightly as fully believe that we feel a sincere friendship for each other ; and let it be lasting as our lives. I regret the separation which probably must soon take place ; but God grant it may be a short one.','ltr_tip4956.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life Timothy Pickering. by His Son, Octavius Pickering. Volume I. 1867');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_tip4957','letter','1775-10-16','Salem','MA','US','Timothy','Pickering','','Samuel','Holten','','individual','','I cannot forbear expressing my surprise at the principle advanced by a certain gentleman, with respect to the appointment of civil officers.','ltr_tip4957.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life Timothy Pickering. by His Son, Octavius Pickering. Volume I. 1867');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_tip4958','letter','1776-01-31','Salem','MA','US','Timothy','Pickering','','George','Washington','','individual','','We were therefore induced to try another method, and the Committee of Safety gave the enlisting orders to a worthy man and good soldier who had served as a Lieutenant in the army the last campaign, and offered a month\'s pay in advance to all who would enlist under him.','ltr_tip4958.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life Timothy Pickering. by His Son, Octavius Pickering. Volume I. 1867');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_tip4959','letter','1777-01-12','Danbury','CT','US','Timothy','Pickering','','Rebecca','Pickering','','individual','','I arrived at Danbury on Thursday night, the 2d of January, in company with General Lincoln, who, going on the next day for Peekskill, directed me to tarry here, to forward the militia as they arrived.','ltr_tip4959.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life Timothy Pickering. by His Son, Octavius Pickering. Volume I. 1867');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_tip4960','letter','1777-01-14','Bedford','NY','US','Timothy','Pickering','','Rebecca','Pickering','','individual','','Yesterday I walked from Danbury to this place twenty long miles in company with Mr. Cabot and two other gentlemen.','ltr_tip4960.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life Timothy Pickering. by His Son, Octavius Pickering. Volume I. 1867');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_tip4961','letter','1777-04-09','Salem','MA','US','Timothy','Pickering','','George','Washington','','individual','','I esteem it a singular honor done me by your Excellency in offering me the post of Adjutant-General ; and it pains me sensibly that I am obliged to decline it.','ltr_tip4961.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life Timothy Pickering. by His Son, Octavius Pickering. Volume I. 1867');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_tip4962','letter','1777-04-14','Salem','MA','US','Timothy','Pickering','','George','Washington','','individual','','I sent, by the express, an answer to your letter respecting the office of Adjutant-General, and gave what appeared to me sufficient reasons to excuse my declining to accept it ; but I have since been uneasy lest you should deem them otherwise','ltr_tip4962.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life Timothy Pickering. by His Son, Octavius Pickering. Volume I. 1867');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_tip4963','letter','1777-05-07','Boston','MA','US','Timothy','Pickering','','George','Washington','','individual','','And since, notwithstanding all my objections, tis your Excellency\'s pleasure, I am happy to declare my acceptance of it. At the same time, I am constrained, from my real feelings, again to express my fears that I shall fall short of your Excellency\'s expectations.','ltr_tip4963.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life Timothy Pickering. by His Son, Octavius Pickering. Volume I. 1867');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_tip4964','letter','1777-05-23','Middlebrook','NJ','US','Timothy','Pickering','','Rebecca','Pickering','','individual','','I embrace the first opportunity since my arrival here to write you. I am very happy in the General\'s family. His secretaries and aides-de-camp are gentlemen of education, and of the most polite, obliging manners.','ltr_tip4964.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life Timothy Pickering. by His Son, Octavius Pickering. Volume I. 1867');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_tip4965','letter','1777-07-06','Morristown','NJ','US','Timothy','Pickering','','Rebecca','Pickering','','individual','','The enemy having entirely quitted Jersey, and the General suspecting they might go up the North River, the army moved up from Middle Brook, last Thursday, to this place, to be nearer to Peekskill.','ltr_tip4965.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life Timothy Pickering. by His Son, Octavius Pickering. Volume I. 1867');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_tip4966','letter','1777-07-26','Morristown','NJ','US','Timothy','Pickering','','Rebecca','Pickering','','individual','','But, having advanced a dozen miles into the Clove, we halted, having reason to doubt, from the enemy\'s movements and the best intelligence we could obtain, whether they were bound up the North River or to the eastward, or not.','ltr_tip4966.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life Timothy Pickering. by His Son, Octavius Pickering. Volume I. 1867');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_tip4967','letter','1777-08-01','Philadelphia','PA','US','Timothy','Pickering','','Rebecca','Pickering','','individual','','Last night the General and his family arrived here. Yesterday morn ing, about half after nine o clock, an express came to the General to inform him of the arrival of the enemy\'s fleet at the Capes of the river.','ltr_tip4967.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life Timothy Pickering. by His Son, Octavius Pickering. Volume I. 1867');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_tip4968','letter','1777-09-25','Potsgrove','PA','US','Timothy','Pickering','','','Pickering','','individual','','Although our loss in the battle of Brandywine was not so great as the enemy\'s, yet since then it has been much larger; I mean by straggling and desertions','ltr_tip4968.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life Timothy Pickering. by His Son, Octavius Pickering. Volume I. 1867');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_tip4969','letter','1777-11-04','Whitemarsh','PA','US','Timothy','Pickering','','Rebecca','Pickering','','individual','','pleased as I am with this proof of your fond affection, I do not wish you to indulge such melancholy thoughts. I know tis difficult to control the mind.','ltr_tip4969.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life Timothy Pickering. by His Son, Octavius Pickering. Volume I. 1867');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_tip4970','letter','1777-11-15','Whitemarsh','PA','US','Timothy','Pickering','','Henry','Laurens','','individual','','I was honored with your favor of the 8th instant, en closing a minute of Congress intimating my appointment to the Board of War.','ltr_tip4970.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life Timothy Pickering. by His Son, Octavius Pickering. Volume I. 1867');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_tip4971','letter','1777-11-18','Whitemarsh','PA','US','Timothy','Pickering','','Rebecca','Pickering','','individual','','Colonel Harrison yesterday went to Reading to see General Mifflin, being in some doubt whether to accept or not. I hope ardently that he will, because he is a sensible, a diligent, a most worthy, honest man','ltr_tip4971.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life Timothy Pickering. by His Son, Octavius Pickering. Volume I. 1867');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_tip4972','letter','1777-12-21','Valley Forge','PA','US','Timothy','Pickering','','Rebecca','Pickering','','individual','','You tell me you embraced the opportunity by Mr. Goodhue to write to me, though you had nothing new to acquaint me with ; and yet you filled up nearly three pages.','ltr_tip4972.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life Timothy Pickering. by His Son, Octavius Pickering. Volume I. 1867');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_tip4973','letter','1777-12-24','Valley Forge','PA','US','Timothy','Pickering','','Rebecca','Pickering','','individual','','How many parents hearts have been rent with grief, how many widowed mates, how many spotless virgins (like the drooping lilies), have bowed their heads, oppressed with sorrow, at the loss of children, husbands, lovers !','ltr_tip4973.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life Timothy Pickering. by His Son, Octavius Pickering. Volume I. 1867');
